        <body>
            <!-- pg 3 -->
            <pb facs="bunting-nb-p3.jpg"/>
            <p>The wear frozen over: dozens of blackheaded gulls sitting on the snow-covered ice: the
                buildings above the bare trees.</p>
            
            
            <p>A burn from the goaf--'steep', of an eye</p>
            
            
            <p>If the goaf be one's heart? soul? unconscious?</p>
            
            
            <p>Muck from the goaf</p>
            
            <!-- pg 4 -->
            <pb facs="bunting-nb-p4.jpg"/>
            <lg type="extract">
                <l>--they knew not</l>
                <l>That what I motion<del>e</del><add>'</add>d was of God; I knew</l>
                <l>From intimate impulse...</l>
            </lg>
            
            <p><title resp="#Milton">Samson Agonistes</title></p>
            
            <l>A deep, booming voice, and words</l>
            <l>like flakes of snow [Odysseus]-- Il<del>l</del>iad 3</l>
            
            <l>Turmoil of her hair––<w cert="low">Ousori</w></l>
            
            <l>Flowers of oak, broom, meadowsweet</l>
            <l>= <choice>
                <orig>Blodeuedd</orig>
                <reg>Blodeuwedd</reg>
            </choice></l>
            <l>(wife of Lleu)</l>
            
            <!-- pg 5 -->
            <pb facs="bunting-nb-p5.jpg"/>
            <p>(<date>April</date>)</p>
            
            <l>A thread net drapes and creases the <precision cert="low"/>haugh,</l>
            <l>crackled glaze fired by dexterous suns.</l>
            <l>What use? Elegant hope, fever of tune,</l>
            <l>new now, next, in the fall, to be dust.</l>
            
            <p><date when="1969">1969</date></p>
            <p>?straw?</p>
            
        </body>
